@node Bytekiller "ByteKiller V2.0"

ByteKiller V2.0 is XIM Tool for /X 3.+ and /X 4.+

What can Bytekiller :

You can start Bytekiller with "Nuke trsi* afl*.dms fake*.l*.txt"

Bytekiller search if the ToolType @{BG fill}@{"NUKER_ALL" link ToolTypes}@{BG Background}
is installed or if there any Tooltypes looks like @{BG fill}@{"NUKER.<x>" link ToolTypes}@{BG Background} or @{BG fill}@{"PASSWORD.<x>" link ToolTypes}@{BG Background}

If there is NUKER_ALL, bytekiller starts for all who wanted to nuke and 
have the right level,
else bytekiller search for the right name and if he have any PW-protection`s !

Bytekiller can write only one message to the Up-Downloader about all fakes

If bytekiller doesn`t can Lock Msgbase or Filelist, he wait a while and if 
there is no chance for Lock, he aborted this routine..

You can Configure all Comments and Messages how ever you want..please 
search in @{BG fill}@{"Configuration" link mycfg}@{BG Background} for that

Bytekiller can search for hisself about Dl- and UlPathes or Path to Callerslog 
and any more, but it is important to install the Tooltype @{BG fill}@{"USER_DATA" link ToolTypes}@{BG Background}
because I handle this for myself because some stupid changes in /X 4.+

Bytekiller can open an ASL-Requester if you have installed the Tooltype @{BG fill}@{"ASK_ASL" link ToolTypes}@{BG Background}
but this Option works only if you nuked from the Console..

Bytekiller have some extern Tools, if you use any of them you have the fastest
Nuker of the world...

You can set up All Options in Bytekiller !

                           @{BG fill}@{"Start von Bytekiller"   link start_bytekiller}@{BG Background}

@endnode
@node start_bytekiller "ByteKiller V2.0"

Start Bytekiller V2.0 :

if you started bytekiller he ask (if exist) for the Password from the User,
than he shows, if there any UserComments about some fakes and ask if 
you want to Nuke from List !
You can Insert so many Files you ever want with and without Wildcarts !
Now Bytekiller Ask you if you want to nuke with Automodus and if you want to 
use the same options for all Files.....
if you use Automodus, you can set options for all files or options 
from file to file.
now Ask Bytekiller if you are interested to search for UpLoader and 
show you his status if he have found the User..
You can take or give now so many Creditz you ever want..
If you have done this, bytekiller ask you to search for Downloader
and do show you his status and ask if he can have some bytes back..
If that is Ok you can set up the comments for the Filelisting !

Now Bytekiller changes the listing writes some messages to the 
Up-Downloader and ask you if you want to give some extra comments 
in that message (if you have install the Tooltype "EXTERN_COMMENT") !

                              @{BG fill}@{"   ByteKiller V2.0    "   link Bytekiller}@{BG Background}
                              @{BG fill}@{"ToolTypes" link ToolTypes}@{BG Background}
@endnode

@node ByteComment "ByteComment V1.0"

ByteComment V1.0 is XIM for /X 3+ 

This Tool is for all User to add some comments in your Filelisting,
this comments are saved in your bytekiller/fakes/ dir and if you 
started Bytekiller and he found some Comments, he ask you to use this list !

                              @{BG fill}@{"       Menue          "   link main}@{BG Background}
                              @{BG fill}@{"   ByteKiller V2.0    "   link Bytekiller}@{BG Background}
                              @{BG fill}@{"ToolTypes" link ToolTypes}@{BG Background}
@endnode

@node Bytekillhandler "Bytekillhandler V1.0"

Bytekillhandler is an external CLI-Tool to start in your logoff-batch, 
if you use this Tool, you doesn`t need to run ByteLog. 

this Handler search in your Callerslog for any Uploads from the last user
and saves his AccountNumber, this Handler doesn`t need DataFiles for that,
so it doesn`t need any bytes from your HD`s

my tip : start bytekillhandler before all other in your Logoff-batch !

example for logoff-batch:
----------------------------
.key node

Doors:Bytekilller/bytekillhandler BBS:node<node>/Callerslog

---------------------------------------------------------------------------

                           @{BG fill}@{"       Menue          "   link main}@{BG Background}
                           @{BG fill}@{"   ByteKiller V2.0    "   link Bytekiller}@{BG Background}
@endnode

@node Bytelog "Bytelog V1.0"

ByteLog is XIM Tool for /X 3.+

You can start it with EXAMINE.INFO
                      EXAMINE1.INFO .....  (/X 4.+)
                      FILECHECK.INFO
                      FILECHECK1.INFO .... (/X 4.+)
in your SYSCMD/

it saves the user and his Upload in one dataFile in your Conf,you can 
say how many days you want to Log if you install @{BG fill}@{"LOG_DAYS=<tage>" link ToolTypes}@{BG Background}
in your bytekiller.info, default is 7 days !

ByteLog doesn`t strip the UdLog, he search, if there is an Upload witch
is older than your Log Days and overwrite this data !

if you run this Door you doesn`t need Bytekillhandler !

                              @{BG fill}@{"       Menue          "   link main}@{BG Background}
                              @{BG fill}@{"   ByteKiller V2.0    "   link Bytekiller}@{BG Background}
                              @{BG fill}@{"ToolTypes" link ToolTypes}@{BG Background}
@endnode

