@node mycfg "All Informations about Configuration(s)"

Configuration from the messages :


%L  ----->  List of all Fakes and Up-Download Day with 
            creditz taken/Given

%N ------>  Name of the Nuker 

%F ------>  Name of the Faker or Downloader

%T ------>  All bytes taken in this Session.......
            (ONLY FOR UPLOADER.CFG)               
          
%G ------>  All bytes Given in this Session.......
            (ONLY FOR UPLOADER.CFG)               

%B ------>  All Dl-Bytes given back in this Session.......
            (ONLY FOR DOWNLOADER.CFG)               

example :
----------


Hey %F you are Lame ,
I have taken you %T because some fakes.., here is a list of all

%L

             please Delete this Message !

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
means :

Hey byteandi/trsi you are lame,
I have taken you 32228 bytes because some fakes.., here is the list of all

Old UpLoad Bytes   :                         8738
Bytekiller V2.0    : Nuked *( -5)              71  Uploaded on (10-23-94)
LamerDoc.txt       : Nuked *( -5)              71  Uploaded on (10-23-94)
-------------------------------------------------
New UpLoad Bytes   :                            1

             please Delete this Message !

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Configuration for your Comments in the Filelisting :

%b  ---->  how many Creditz Taken/given
%B  ---->  bytes from the Nuked File
%N  ---->  Name of the Nuker

Example :

Enter FakeComment : ^^ %N Takes you %B Bytes * (%b) ^^

means :

                    ^^ Byteandi/trsi Takes you 32321 Bytes * (-5) ^^



                              @{BG fill}@{"       Menue          "   link main}@{BG Background}
                              @{BG fill}@{"   ByteKiller V2.0    "   link Bytekiller}@{BG Background}
                              @{BG fill}@{"ToolTypes" link ToolTypes}@{BG Background}


@endnode

@node ToolTypes "All Informations about ToolTypes"



USER_DATA         -----> Path and Name from  UserData

NUKER_ALL         -----> this means that there is no PW protection,
                         All User with the right Level can nuke

NUKER.<x>=<name>  -----> the name of the User who can Nuke 
                         x = Number from 1 to ..

PASSWORD.<x>=<PW> -----> The Password from the User who can Nuke
                         x = Number from 1 to ..

ANSI_MESSAGE      -----> if you doesn`t use this Tooltype, Bytekiller striped
                         All Ansi-Codes in the messages...

COMMENT.x=<wieviel> ---> Comment for the Filelisting (default`s)
                         x = Number from 1 to ..                 

FAKE.<x>=<warum>  -----> Why you have Nuked the File (default`s)
                         x = Number from 1 to ..                 

SIZE.<x>=<shit!>  -----> Comments for the ByteSize in the Listing 
                         x = Number from 1 to ..                 

FREE_COLOR=<36>   -----> Color for the Comment if you make the File to 
                         freedownload
                         
GIVE_COLOR=<32>   -----> Color for the Comment if you Give Creditz 
                         

TAKE_COLOR=<44;39> ----> Color for the Comment if you Take Creditz 
                         

EXTERN_COMMENT    -----> if you have this Toolstype, bytekiller ask
                         if you want to write some lines to the 
                         Up-Downloader

CREATE_FAKEFILE   -----> you can create Fakefiles if you want..

ASK_ASL           -----> Bytekiller ask you if you want to use an 
                         ASl-Requester to flag files

SPY_LIST=<list>   -----> ONLY to use if you have installed SPY_LIST
                         or you have the files and descriptions in more
                         FileListings, than list = the last list of deleted
                         Files..
FREEDOWNLOAD=<text>  --> text = what ever you want to give as Comment in 
                         your Listing default is :
                         "FREEDOWNLOAD FREEDOWNLOAD"

LOG_DAYS=<days>   -----> for ByteLog, to say how many Days he must Log !
                         

COM_COLOR=<44;39> -----> Color for ByteComment

                              @{BG fill}@{"       Menue          "   link main}@{BG Background}
                              @{BG fill}@{"   ByteKiller V2.0    "   link Bytekiller}@{BG Background}
                              @{BG fill}@{"ToolTypes" link ToolTypes}@{BG Background}
@endnode

